post_text:
Interested in playing 7th and 8th grade girls basketball this fall? There will be open gyms this Monday August 3rd , Wednesday August 5th, and Thursday August 6th from 10:30 am – 12 pm at the High School Gymnasium.

For any questions, please contact Coach J. Ponsoll (ponsollj@flbapps.net) Coach Hughes (hughesr@flbapps.net) or Coach Burchanowski (burchanowskit@flbapps.net) . Please make sure to follow all physical distancing and masking guidelines.

Physicals for ALL girls basketball players will take place at the High School on Thursday August 6th at 9:30 am. Remember, any athlete wishing to participate in a sport must receive a physical before the 1st day of practice!

#FLBHS #gobison #bisonpride

The 2020 Commencement Ceremony be taking place tonight at the Sunset Drive In, the gates will open at 8 p.m., the private showing for FLB Graduates and families will start at 9:20 p.m.

Please remember the following:

One car per graduate permitted, please have your ticket placed on your dashboard.

Social distance guidelines are in place and need to be implemented.

Parking is first come, first serve.

We hope that you enjoy the evening!

Any students who need mental health support can reach out to our school counselors in several ways. Through email: Mrs. Gadley – gadleyc@flbapps.net, Mrs. Uveges – uvegesc@flbapps.net, or Mrs. Lutzo – lutzoa@flbapps.net

All students have been invited through email to sign into their Google Classroom - FLB School Counseling Services - for more resources and support.

They also each have virtual office hours. Students can sign up through SignUpGenius:

Mrs. Gadley - https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040b49afa828a1fb6-mrs

Mrs. Uveges - https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10c0844aaac2fa1f58-mrs

Mrs. Lutzo - https://www.signupgenius.com/go/30e0d4eaba922abf94-flbschool

#mentalhealthawarenessmonth #aksforhelpifyouneedit #oneherdonefamily

post_text:
Senior Spotlight!

Brandon Mackowski plans on entering the Navy after graduation, he is set to start basic training in late September. Brandon will be training as an Aviation Ordnanceman, where we will be learning to organize, arm, and store missiles and ammunition used by Aircraft. Brandon would like to share the following message, “I am very excited for this new chapter in my life, but I will never forget those around me who brought me this far, all I can say is thank you!” Thank you for your commitment and Congratulations Brandon!

#FLBHS #gobison #bisonpride #leavealegacy

Any students who need mental health support can reach out to our school counselors in several ways. Through email: Mrs. Gadley – gadleyc@flbapps.net, Mrs. Uveges – uvegesc@flbapps.net, or Mrs. Lutzo – lutzoa@flbapps.net

All students have been invited through email to sign into their Google Classroom - FLB School Counseling Services - for more resources and support.

They also each have virtual office hours. Students can sign up through SignUpGenius:

Mrs. Gadley - https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040b49afa828a1fb6-mrs

Mrs. Uveges - https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10c0844aaac2fa1f58-mrs

post_text:
Both graduation speakers and singers recorded their performances today. Mr. Rimpa, our principal, and Mrs. Humphreys, our senior class advisor, are working hard preparing the graduation ceremony for the Class of 2020. Along with the students, Mr. Gerard, the emcee, Mr. Hordusky, our school board president, and Mr. Emerick, our superintendent, also participated in today's filming.

Speakers include Faculty Choice Rachel Daum, Valedictorian Lucas Mosher, Salutatorian Andrew Crilley, Class Choice Brandon Ossa, and Class President Gabi Cook. Evelynn Bengel and Elena Bengel are our singers.

The small group followed all of the current safety precautions, wearing masks and sitting six feet apart. Everyone also had their temperature taken by the school nurse as they entered the building. #bisonpride #leavealegacy #Classof2020 #stayingsafe

post_text:
Here is a great workout to add your exercise regime, from Football Booster Club Strength and Conditioning Coach Goodwin:

Monday-

Bb squats 5x5, Db lunges 5x5, Bb Deadlifts 5x5,, Wide Chins 4x failure, Bb arm curls 5x5, Abs-100 reps

Tuesday-

Bb Flat 5x5, Bb push press 5x5, Db flat flys 5x5, 2 arm Bb tricep extensions 5x5, Db rear laterals 5x5

Thursday

Bb front squats 5x5, Bb stiff legs 5x5, Db one arm rows 5x5, Db arm curls 5x5, Abs-100

Friday

Bb incline bench 5x5, Db incline flys 5x5, Db side laterals 5x5, Bb uprights 5x5, Bb close grip bench 5x5, 5x5 reps you will be using as much weight as possible for the 5 sets

Continue to stay focused on eating healthy as always!

#FLBHS #gobison #bisonpride

Senior Spotlight!

Emily Yaple will be pursuing a degree in Business at the University of Pittsburgh, as well as playing Division I Soccer for the University. Emily was able to start training and taking classes at Pitt in January after successfully completing her studies at Fort LeBoeuf and Gannon University. Emily was rostered to play soccer with the WPSL Pittsburgh Hotspurs this season; however, the virus has caused the season to be canceled. Congratulations Emily!

Hunter Yaple has committed to Gannon University to play Division II Soccer. Hunter is a daunting goalie at 6’ 2” and looks forward to being a Golden Knight! He is pursuing a degree in Cyber Engineering and Cyber Security. Hunter is also an “essential” employee at St. Vincent hospital where he has been employed for 1 1/2 years. Hunter will also be completing the ECTS Computer Networking Program at the end of the 2019-2020 school year. Congratulations Hunter!

post_text:
Senior Spotlight!

Emily Kucenski will be attending Penn State University in the fall and majoring in Kinesiology. After completion of her bachelor’s degree, Emily’s goal is to pursue a career as a Physical Therapist. Congratulations Emily!

Emily encourages her fellow seniors to reflect on the time they have spent together, and to put the premature end to their senior year in perspective. “Even though our senior milestones have been lost, I realize that it was a small price to pay knowing that my teachers and classmates are safe. For now, I will make the most of the time I have with my family before I leave for college and once all of this is over, I will never again take for granted time with friends.”

#FLBHS #gobison #bisonpride #leavealegacy

post_text:
Here is this week's home work-out plan from FLB football booster strength and conditioning coach Mike Goodwin:

Monday- Squats-6,6,4,4, Db lunge 4x8, Bb Deadlifts 6,6,4,4, Db one arm rows 6,6,4,4, Bb arm curls 8,8,6,6 , Abs

In an effort to provide communication to our students and families, Mr. Rimpa and Mr. Pizzo have decided to start a weekly program to provide information regarding the continuous updates that are occuring during this challenging time.

The Bison Broadcast will occur on Wednesdays at 11 a.m. weekly, at the end of each Bison Broadcast, there will be a link provided where questions can be submitted and they will be answered during the following week’s program.

We hope that this provides a sense of connection for our students, families, and community members that we are all longing for.

Please use the following link to access today’s Bison Broadcast, https://youtu.be/bj3mMHk6OuQ?t=12

post_text:
Here are some ideas for your home workouts, from Mike Goodwin, FLB Football Booster Strength & Conditioning Coach.

If you don’t have access to free weights try…
-Walking lunges
-Push ups, with different hand placements
-Wide grip chin ups
-Reverse grip biceps pulls ups
-Isometric push/pull with towels or ropes for tricep & bicep work
-Any core training i.e. sit ups, crunches, planks of all varieties etc…

If you do have access to free weights/barbell or dumbbells reach out to Coach Goodwin and he can give you some exercises.

As always, keep up your nutrition, this is a good time to pack on the pounds!

#FLBHS #bisonpride #gobison

post_text:
This is just a reminder to students and staff at the high school that we have EBSCOhost databases for research. Instead of just Googling a topic you are interested in learning about, you can EBSCOhost search it and get access to thousands of resources that have been vetted and organized for you. We have access to thousands of periodicals, academic journals, eBooks, maps, photographs, newspapers, radio and television transcripts, and primary source documents. (Are you journaling about our current situation? Your writings could be primary source documents for future researchers.)

Access EBSCOhost from the high school library page of our district website or the Bookmarks on your Chromebook. Don't forget you will need an additional login and password to get in outside of the high school building. Email Mrs. Tarr to get it at tarra@flbapps.net

Follow the HUB on Instagram at flb_hs_hub

#bisonstrong #oneherdonefamily #smartbison #EXPLORE #INQUIRE

Please note that Governor Wolf’s Stay-at-Home order does not prohibit school districts from continuing to offer food services to children during the statewide school closure. We cannot thank our food service team enough for all of the hard work they have put into keeping this important opportunity available for our families and their children.

FLB will only be distributing meals on Mondays & Thursday each week.
Meal Pickup Times Are The Following:
Fort LeBoeuf High School – 11 am till 1 pm & 4:30 pm till 6:30 pm
Robison Elementary School – 11 am till 1 pm
Mill Village Elementary School – 11 am till 1 pm

Additional PM pickup at the FLB High School is for families who are unable to pick up during the day time meal pickup process remains the same Breakfast & Lunch Meals will still be distributed at those times Mondays you will receive 3 Breakfast & 3 Lunch Meals per child Thursdays you will receive 2 Breakfast & 2 Lunch Meals per child.

Please contact Chef Tech with any questions, 814-796-4795.

#bisonpride #leavealegacy #oneherd

The VFW Post 740 Edinboro-McKean Senior Scholarship application deadline has been extended two weeks to Wednesday, April 15th. Completed applications are to be mailed directly to Post 740. Yesterday, members of LeadFLB and their Advisors, Mrs. Ransom and Mrs. Adams, held the quarterly award assembly during tutorial. Only students earning a Platinum Blue or White Gold card were invited to participate. The criteria for the cards are based on quarterly grades, attendance, and discipline.

The prizes that were raffled off included Fort Leboeuf apparel from The Fort, coupons and gift certificates to local businesses, and even a Spikeball Set! Junior, Max Endres was the lucky winner of the Spikeball Set. The third quarter LeadFLB assembly is right around the corner in April, so make sure you don't miss out on the opportunity to win some great prizes!

post_text:
Current and former students of Ms. Lazor’s Spanish classes who started learning the basics of mindfulness and meditation in class, continued developing their practice last Wednesday. Local therapist and yoga instructor Nea Motzer, of her own Soul Blossom Erietherapy/yoga studio in Erie, lead the students in an hour-long meditation and yin yoga practice and reflection.

Yin yoga is a slow-paced style of yoga where asanas (poses) are held for 1-2 minutes each with slow breathing to increase flexibility, circulation, and when mixed with meditation — cultivate inner stillness. A huge shoutout to Nea for coming down to Fort LeBouf to help us get our ‘ohm’ on!! Namaste!

#FLBHS #gobison #bisonpride

post_text:
Thank you, FLB Alumni, Andrew Gallagher, for coming in and speaking to Mr. Shesman’s Honors Algebra II class today about his career journey and career opportunities that are math and computer science related.

Andrew graduated from FLB in 1992, from there he attended Geneva College for Electrical Engineering. After graduating Andrew worked for Kodak, which lead him to pursue his Masters Degree in Electrical Engineering. After completing that program, he worked in the field, for a start up company and completed his Ph.D. at Carnegie Mellon University. Andrew has been working in Google Research for the past 5 years in a Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence. To check out some of Andrew’s past projects, visit http://chenlab.ece.cornell.edu/people/Andy/.

We’re proud to have been named to the College Board’s 10th Annual AP ® District Honor Roll for
our efforts to expand access to AP coursework and improve student performance on AP Exams. The Honor Roll recognizes 250 school districts in the U.S. and Canada that have increased access to AP coursework while maintaining or increasing the percentage of students earning scores of 3 or higher. post_text:
The Fort LeBoeuf Leo Club donated five new books about kindness and mindfulness to the high school library. The Leo Club’s themes for the year are #kindnessmatters and #everyonehasastory. Activities planned for the school year include ways to encourage empathy among students and staff. As Atticus Finch told his daughter Scout in To Kill a Mockingbird, “You never really understand a person until you consider things from his point of view…until you climb into his skin and walk around in it.” Everyone has a story, and we can’t possibly know what’s going on with individual people just by looking at them. We need to take that extra moment to smile and say good morning. Little things can make big differences to people. These books include many suggestions for those small but important acts of kindness and ways to help ourselves and others. #SHARE #INCLUDE #servingothers #leoclub #bisonpride #leavealegacy #DoGoodDecember
Pictured: Secretary/Treasurer Andie O’Neill, Caitlin Riley, President April Barringer, Nicole Segal, & Madison Cidor
